TheBattle of Agincourtwas a major English victory in theHundred Years' War.Ref labelaanoneThe battle took place on Friday, 25 October 1415 (Saint Crispin's Day), near modern-dayAzincourt, in northern France.sfnde Monstrelet1853340Ref labelbbnoneHenry V of EnglandHenry V's victory at Agincourt, against a numerically superior French army, crippled France and started a new period in the war during which Henry V married theCatherine of ValoisFrench king's daughter, and their son, laterDual monarchy of England and FranceHenry VI of England and Henry II of France, was made heir to the throne of France as well as of England.
